Arsenal, Inc., the premier American importer and manufacturer of semi-auto rifles, is proud to offer to American shooters the new addition to the SAM7 family – the SAM7UF rifle. This 7.62x39 caliber rifle combines authentic, high-quality features expected in the SAM7 Family. From its reinforced under-folding buttstock to its 14x1mm left hand muzzle threads with muzzle nut, every component of the SAM7UF is engineered to provide decades of dependable and accurate service. The SAM7UF rifle is bound to become a sought-after and collectible firearm.

The New Reinforced Under-Folding Stock
The SAM7UF utilizes the modern straight-back under-folding stock, which locks perpendicular to the action and the bore of the rifle. In order to provide a more secure and firm lock, whether in a folded or extended position, this stock locks on both sides of the receiver with 4 solid pins. The reinforced, straight-back folding stock stabilizes the rifle which significantly reduces the climb and gives the shooter much firmer control over the firearm for improved accuracy and effectiveness. These are major improvements over its predecessor, the tilt-down stock, and this rifle will surely exceed it. 

Arsenal’s Exclusive Milled And Forged Receiver
Each SAM7UF receiver is milled from a hot-die hammer forged receiver blank by the Arsenal Co. of Bulgaria. Other milled-receiver AKs are machined from bar stock, but Arsenal’s hot-die hammer forging produces stronger and finer-grained steel. Internal voids and cooling deformations are eliminated by the 5-ton hammer forging process. 

Each forged receiver blank requires over 5.5 hours of milling before assembly. This forging and milling process is complex and time-intensive, but Arsenal’s meticulous attention to detail delivers a receiver of unequalled strength, precision, and durability.

title: For Sale:  AR 15 Carbine and AR 15 Pistol 5.56/.223 16" and 7.5" barrel
postcontent:
Pictures 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5 are all the components necessary to make up your AR Carbine or AR Pistol, except the stripped lower receiver which you must provide. When you decide to purchase this kit, I will build the lower receiver that you have provided, while you watch. It will take approx. 30-45 minutes for this build at which time you will have a complete Carbine, or Pistol that you are able to take away. Both the Carbine and the Pistol uppers have been test fired to ensure they strip the rounds properly from the magazine, feed those rounds into the chamber, fire the rounds effectively, extract the spent casing from the chamber and then eject that spent casing from the weapon. If it did not do any of the functioning tasks correctly, consistently, it would not be here for sale at this time. With your built lower, these weapons are ready for whatever........

AR 15 Carbine are pictures 1 and 2.......This Carbine has a 16" barrel with a "wylde" chamber which is specially made to accept both .223 and 5.56 rounds and is from Maric Arms, it is made from parkerized steel and has a twist rate of 1:8. The compensator is a dragon head sound and flash director. The upper receiver is from SAA and is forged from Mil-Spec 7075 T-6 Aluminum and has M4 feedramps. The Bolt Carrier and Bolt are from SAA and are of excellent quality. The handguard is a Yankee Hill Free Floating Diamond series Spectre length (9.675"). The gas block is low profile standard aluminum and the gas tube is carbine length at 9.75". 

The lower will be built with a standard Lower Parts Kit from Aero, but the different grip you will get, instead of the standard BS grip, is pictured. The different trigger guard that you will get is pictured, and is a polymer curved guard for room for a gloved finger, and not the standard BS straight trigger guard.

AR Pistol is picture 3.......This Pistol has a 7.5" barrel with a "wylde" chamber which is specially made to accept both .223 and 5.56 rounds and it is from Maric Arms, it is made from parkerized steel and has a twist rate of 1:7. The compensator is a sound and flash director made by Kineti-Tech. The upper receiver is from SAA and is forged from Mil-Spec 7075 T-6 Aluminum and has M4 feedramps. The Bolt Carrier and Bolt are from SAA and are of excellent quality. The handguard is a Yankee Hill Free Floating Diamond series Carbine length (7.290"). The gas block is low profile standard aluminum and the gas tube is pistol length at 6.75".

The lower will be built with a standard Lower Parts Kit from Aero, but the different grip you will get, instead of the standard BS grip, is pictured. The different trigger guard that you will get is pictured, and is a polymer curved guard for room for a gloved finger, and not the standard BS straight trigger guard.

Picture #4 shows a 16" Carbine length upper that has the same components as the 16" listed above, except, the full float hanguard is not a Yankee Hill and the flash suppressor is a standard A2 birdcage. All else is the same as explained above. It can be purchased the same way with your "supplied" upper built and attached, or as a complete upper (as pictured) only. Your choice.

Picture #5 shows a 7" AR Pistol upper. This upper has a Karri's Arms upper receiver made from Mil-Spec 7075 T-6 Aluminum with M4 feed ramps. The barrel is a Karri's Arms 5.56 Nato 1:7 twist 7" parkerized barrel. There is a "Devestator" muzzle break. The bolt carrier and bolt are both from Karri's Arms and is of high quality. The gas key is properly staked. The barrel is full floating with a generic aluminum handguard. This Pistol upper can be purchased as a complete upper only, or, can be combined with a complete lower receiver build with "your" supplied stripped lower as the others above are described as well.

All of these weapons are of quality parts and would retail at a brick and mortar store for approx. $900-$950, maybe more.

My price to you, for everything you see pictured is...... for the Carbine (pictures 1 and 2) $675 and the Pistol (picture 3) $650. The Carbine in picture 4 is $560 complete with the same items you see in pictures 1, 2 and 3. The Pistol in picture 5 is $540 complete with the same items you see in pictures 1, 2 and 3. These prices are all inclusive of building "your" stripped lower and then connecting the upper to the lower, handing it to you for your immediate possession. If you have "other" parts you would like for me to add then let me know and this will be done at the same time.

If you are interested in the upper only (and have your own lower to use) then the prices for the Carbine upper (pictures 1 and 2) complete is $540 and the Pistol upper in picture 3 is $520. The Carbine upper in picture 4 is $420. The Pistol upper in picture 5 is $400.

title: For Sale/Trade:  SS Interarms Walther PPK - 4 Mags - LOWERED Price
location: Eastside (Hyde Park, Madisonville, Oakley), Cincinnati, Ohio
postcontent:
Hi All,

Up for sale is my stainless steel Walther PPK, assembled by Interarms, which are regarded as being better than the later S&W ones.

This gun is in great shape, no rust or damage, just slight wear you'd expect from an older gun. It will come with 4 magazines, all quality mags that work 100%. 

I have a LH IWB Tagua holster I'd throw in as well. Plus, an unused LH OWB Bianchi holster for an extra $20. I realize this won't be for everyone since holsters are very personal, and I'm a lefty...

I've been consolidating into just 9mm and 45ACP, and this is my only gun left in 380 Auto, the only reason I'm getting rid of this sweet piece.

I had a few issues with the slide not returning to battery, and read up on it. People said the factory 20# spring may not allow the slide to travel back far enough, not giving it enough oomph (technical term here) to return to battery. Swapping in a Wolff 17# spring would correct that. So I did, and it's been 100% reliable since, even with crappy steel cased Tula. I still have the original factory spring I'll include.

I also have approximately 600 rounds of ammo that I'll sell. 200 WWB FMJ, 100 Prvi FMJ, 100 Brassmaxx FMJ, 50 Perfecta FMJ, partial box of Aguila FMJ, partial box of Tula FMJ, 100 HPR HPs, and 24 loose Federal HPs. I'll do 40 cents per round on the FMJ, and 60 cents per round on the HP. I think that's beyond fair, and probably a bit cheaper than you could get all of this new. Buy all the ammo for $250 extra.

What else can I say? The timeless design of this gun speaks for itself. It's still sexy decades after it's design. This is the James Bond gun after all!

Cash is king, but I'm not opposed to trades. NO JUNK! No offense, but I don't own crap now, and I'm not planning on it in the future. Only interested in pistols in 9mm or 45ACP, or rifles in 5.56/223 or 7.62x39. Would consider a sweet hunting rifle though.

Email me on here, or call/text me @ 5 one 3 - four 6 zero - 5 two 7 two.

Thanks for looking.

NOT FOR SALE WHERE PROHIBITED.

PAYMENT & FFL
Visa, Mastercard, money orders, cashier's checks will be gladly accepted. Visa & Mastercard sales will have a 3% fee added to the total. If you’re paying with a personal check, we must wait for the check to clear before we can ship the firearm, this can take between 10-14 days.

Please arrange to have your local FFL dealer fax or email us a signed current copy of their federal firearms license after the sale as all payments and paperwork must be received within 7 days of the end of auction. It is not our responsibility to contact them. If you cannot comply with that, then please do not bid.

Washington state residents will be charged 8% sales tax. This is not an option.

SHIPPING
Buyer pays the shipping cost listed in the auction (this includes insurance). Handguns are shipped using Registered Mail or Priority Mail depending on the amount of insurance required. Long guns are shipped via UPS Ground, FedEx, or Parcel Pro.

If you live in Washington State, then you can come and pick the item up to waive the shipping cost. All other areas, the buyer must arrange for the item to be shipped to a local FFL holder. Buyer must e-mail or fax a signed, current copy of the FFL holder's license before item may be shipped.

Due to shipping regulations, some restrictions may apply.

U.S. sales only.

LEGAL REQUIREMENTS
All firearms must be transferred through a licensed FFL dealer in your area. The bidder is required to supply a current, signed copy of their local dealer's license before shipment. It is the buyer's responsibility to find out if there are any special regulations in their area before bidding.

All firearms, including antique/black powder, require FFL paperwork and will be shipped to an FFL dealer. No exceptions!

Sorry, no sales California residents, New York, Massachusetts, New Jersey, Hawaii, Alaska, and Illinois.

All state and local laws apply, please be sure you can own the items you are bidding on.

SAFETY NOTICE
The buyer is solely responsible for determining that a used firearm is safe to shoot. The firearms offered have not been test fired. Whether purchased here or somewhere else we urge every buyer to have any used firearm they purchase inspected by a qualified gunsmith before firing.

RETURN POLICY
All firearms come with a 3-day (Monday through Friday) inspection/return privilege. The inspection period begins at the time of delivery to your dealer. It is the buyer's responsibility to inspect the firearm within this time frame. In case of a return, the buyer pays all shipping costs. This does not cover items damaged in shipment; you must save the damaged shipping box and file a claim with the appropriate shipping company. All returned items must be in the exact condition that they left us.
